 first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William De Hywis was born about 1150, in Dunster, Somerset, England, his father, Richard De Hywis, was 1 and his mother, Mrs. Richard De Hywis, was 2. He married Mrs. William De Hywis in 1162. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1185, in his hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"about 1150–1185":"umbes 1150–1185","1150–1185":"1150–1185","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1158–1216":"1158–1216","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","about 1150":"umbes 1150","1216":"1216","1158":"1158","1185":"1185","1130":"1130","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Dunster, Somerset, England":"Dunster, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"about 1150–1185":"noin 1150–1185","1150–1185":"1150–1185","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1158–1216":"1158–1216","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","about 1150":"noin 1150","1216":"1216","1158":"1158","1185":"1185","1130":"1130","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Dunster, Somerset, England":"Dunster, Somerset, England"},"fr":{"about 1150–1185":"environ 1150–1185","1150–1185":"1150–1185","1130–Female":"1130–Décédée","1158–1216":"1158–1216","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1150–Female":"1150–Décédée","about 1150":"environ 1150","1216":"1216","1158":"1158","1185":"1185","1130":"1130","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Angleterre","Dunster, Somerset, England":"Dunster, Somerset, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William De Hywis est né environ 1150, à Dunster, Somerset, Angleterre, son père, Richard De Hywis, avait 1 ans et sa mère, Mrs. Richard De Hywis, avait 2 ans. Il a épousé Mrs. William De Hywis en 1162. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. 